# Implementation Plan - 30-Day Quick Wins

This plan outlines the technical steps to implement the "Quick Win" features for LCMTV: **Continue Watching**, **Daily Verse**, and **Expanded Notifications**.

## User Review Required

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **Database Changes**: This plan requires creating a new table `daily_verses`. Please ensure database migration permissions are available.
> **Push Notifications**: Expanded notifications will use existing VAPID keys. Ensure the server environment variables for `VAPID_PUBLIC_KEY` and `VAPID_PRIVATE_KEY` are correctly set.

## Proposed Changes

---

### 1. Continue Watching Feature
Allow users to resume videos from their last watched position.

#### [MODIFY] [Video.php](file:///c:/xampp/htdocs/LCMTVWebNew/backend/models/Video.php)
- Add `getContinueWatching($userId, $limit = 10)` method.
- This will query the `video_views` table for the most recent record per video for the given user where `watch_percentage < 90` and `completed = 0`.

#### [MODIFY] [VideoController.php](file:///c:/xampp/htdocs/LCMTVWebNew/backend/controllers/VideoController.php)
- Add `getContinueWatching()` action to handle `GET /api/videos/continue-watching`.
- Ensure it requires authentication.

#### [MODIFY] [home.html](file:///c:/xampp/htdocs/LCMTVWebNew/frontend/app/views/pages/home.html)
- Add a new section `Continue Watching` above "Recent Videos" that only appears if the user has incomplete videos.

#### [MODIFY] [HomeController.js](file:///c:/xampp/htdocs/LCMTVWebNew/frontend/app/controllers/HomeController.js)
- Fetch the "Continue Watching" list on initialization.

